    "description": "`ab serve --openai --host 0.0.0.0` exposes an unauthenticated proxy that can invoke local agent CLIs with the user's credentials/config, but the CLI accepts any host string without a separate explicit remote-exposure flag or warning. For local-only tooling, remote binding should require an intentional opt-in such as `--allow-remote`, or reject non-loopback hosts by default."
