    "description": "The missing-required-field check subtracts aliased_required, so an error-correction item that uses a forbidden alias like `incorrect:` without the canonical `error:` will not also report the required `error:` field as missing. The gate still fails, but the diagnostic under-reports the actual schema violation and can steer the writer to rename only one field while leaving malformed item shapes, especially for failure cases where the alias value is a full sentence rather than the misspelled form."
